WEBVTT

00:04:28.160 --> 00:04:30.856
My father did his dental degree
all over again.

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:34.176
And then we ended up
moving to Iowa, of all places.

00:04:34.200 --> 00:04:35.936
We grew up in Iowa.

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:38.336
And in Iowa, we went
through the whole course.

00:04:38.360 --> 00:04:40.816
I went to high school, I went to college.

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:45.896
And then one day,
something that I'll never forget,

00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:50.656
my father picked me up
after my sophomore year in college,

00:04:50.680 --> 00:04:52.016
and he was driving me home,

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:54.176
and he said, "Jim,
what are your aspirations?

00:04:54.200 --> 00:04:56.616
What do you want to study?
What do you want to do?"

00:04:56.640 --> 00:04:57.856
And I said, "Dad," --

00:04:57.880 --> 00:05:01.136
My mother actually was a philosopher,
and had filled us with ideas